OL,6,FPaul Whiteman, general secretary of
OL,7,Fthe National Association of
OL,8,FHeadteachers, said: "We have been
OL,9,Fclear that simplistic one-word
OL,10,Fjudgments are harmful and we are
OL,11,Fpleased the government has taken swift
OL,12,Faction to remove them.
OL,14,F"We are equally pleased that the
OL,15,Fgovernment intends to place a stronger
OL,16,Femphasis on supporting schools to
OL,17,Fimprove where they need help, rather
OL,18,Fthan defaulting to heavy-handed
OL,19,Fintervention or knee-jerk changes of
OL,20,Fgovernance structures."
